content:
The Death and Birth of a New England Madman;
The journey of a man with a beating heart. 
I am cutting deep into the core of things; 
Wouldn’t you like to feel the burning truth?

Born in the woodlands and buried in the dirt;
At the Academy, bound for the Volga.
Learning and listening to classes and truths;
I’m of the frozen coast - I am not those men. 

Determining that directed to be true
This humility - shed for my mastery:
Forgetting that I have forced upon me;
Capturing the crimes that have created me;
Embracing the sins that indeed define me.
